Symptoms:
- “Connection refused” to database
- Service can't connect to PostgreSQL/MariaDB
- “Lost connection to MySQL server”
- Application shows database errors

Diagnosis:
docker ps | grep postgres
docker ps | grep mariadb
docker logs postgres
docker logs mariadb
docker exec postgres pg_isready
docker exec mariadb mysqladmin ping

Common Causes:
- Database container not running
- Database crashed (out of memory)
- Wrong credentials in application config
- Database not ready when application started
- Network connectivity between containers

Solutions:

Restart database:
docker compose restart postgres
# or
docker compose restart mariadb

Check application waits for database:
nano /opt/docker/docker-compose.yml
# Add depends_on if missing:

  [app]:\\
    depends_on:\\
      - postgres\\


Restart application after database is up:
docker compose restart [app]

Check connection string:
# Application should connect to container name, not localhost
# Example: postgres:5432 not localhost:5432

For persistent crashes:
# Check database logs for errors
docker logs postgres –tail 100
# May need to increase database memory limits

Prevention:
- Use depends_on in docker-compose.yml
- Configure health checks
- Monitor database resource usage
- Set appropriate connection timeouts in apps
